Command Git

git init
git add <file(s)>
git status
git commit
git config
git branch
git help
git config --list
git config --global user.email "email"
git config --global user.name "username"
git log --all --decorate --oneline --graph
alias <command>="git log --all --decorate --oneline --graph" => example command
git branch <name> => for add a branch
git checkout <branch name> => for cd branch
git log => for logging 
git merge <branch name> => for merge other branch, but must log on your main branch 
git branch -d <branch name> for delete branch after you merge
git branch -D <branch name> if you want force delete a branch

-----------------------------------------------------
If Clone Repository from Github

git clone <url> => if you want clone repository from github
git pull => if you want update your repository from github

If Change Something
git add <file> or . => for add something you change from your repository
git commit -m "message" or git commit -am "message" => for make a message after you add something to your repo
git push =. to push any change from your repository

-----------------------------------------------------
Note
if your file Modified (M) you can directly commit
if your file Untracked (U) you must add the file before commit

